I need help regarding this issue.

While creating container, I am getting this error 
`FATA[0000] no volume with name roc found in database: no such volume` at https://github.com/containers/libpod/blob/master/libpod/boltdb_state_internal.go#L574

For containerSpec settings are donw in this PR at https://github.com/containers/libpod/pull/1757/files#diff-0ca8a76a233793f50c7f50145a2de951R124

and creation is done with [ImageRootFs](https://github.com/containers/libpod/pull/1757/files#diff-0ca8a76a233793f50c7f50145a2de951R192)

The mount points are set to default one as below.

```
[
  { /proc proc proc      [ nosuid noexec nodev  ]  }   
  { /dev tmpfs tmpfs      [ nosuid strictatime mode=755 size=65536k  ]  }  
  {  /dev/pts devpts devpts      [ nosuid noexec newinstance ptmxmode=0666 mode=0620 gid=5  ]  }   
  {  /dev/shm tmpfs shm      [  nosuid noexec nodev mode=1777 size=65536k   ]  } 
  { /dev/mqueue mqueue mqueue      [  nosuid noexec nodev   ]  }  
  { /sys sysfs sysfs      [ nosuid noexec nodev ro  ]  }   
  { /sys/fs/cgroup cgroup cgroup      [  rprivate nosuid noexec nodev relatime ro  ] }
]
```
This error started coming after #1906 . Is anything changed with this PR, which is required to set with container while creation?

